msContents.summary: Collection of five apparently unpublished comedies by an Italian baroque dramatist. Two of them are librettos for musical dramas.

msItem.title: Il Triunfo della Belleza, Dramma per Musica, p. v

supportDesc.extent: 199 leaves : 266 x 190 mm. bound to 271 x 195 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Paper, i (contemporary paper) + 199 + i (contemporary paper); [viii], 1-390; contemporary pagination in ink, upper outer corners. The fourth folio appears to be a later addition.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in a cursive script by a single hand.

binding.p: Contemporary parchment. Boards badly warped, worn at edges and cracking at hinges and spine. Indications of possible worm damage on spine. Fourth folio very loose. A few light stains and smudges.

origin.p: Written in Perugia or Pistoia, ca. 1695 (Zacour-Hirsch). The latest play in the collection is dated 1695, and the manuscript appears to be contemporary with when the plays were written.

history.provenance: Sold by H.P. Kraus in the Giuseppe Martini collection, ca. 1948.
